Hi to all who may be contemplating Ipnos Relax Melodies App. I have been using the free version for many years now. I had it on my iPhone first, and now I own a phone with android os.  I began using this app because I suffer greatly with a chronic pain disorder, and I also suffer with insomnia and have since I was very young.   I can't tell you all how pleasant it has been to see this app evolve into what it has today. I was so happy when they added binaural beats, then IC tones.  Then, along with all the sounds they keep adding, they added also the timer which has been useful, then the meditations! This went right in line with my therapy. I began taking Dialectical Behavioral Therapy to help me learn to accept my illnesses, (which are more than just the Chronic Pain Disorder, ) and so the meditations began to be a regular part of my everyday battle against pain and it has helped greatly in keeping me on track with meditating and also to be able to meditate on the spot with a shorter meditation during my waking hours to help me re-center myself when the pain takes hold.   I run a page now for chronic pain disorder and for all diseases and other disorders that feature chronic pain. I have for several years been sharing this app with everyone I know, and with people on my page. I encourage everyone to DL this app and purchase the full version for max benefits. Even for those who have a hard time financially, this disorder is highly disabling and let's face it, nobody is getting rich being on disability..   So, I tell my chronic pain community that even if they can not purchase the full version, Ipnos is fortunately for many if us having financial problems due to our illnesses, VERY generous with their free trial version. They are like no other company which tells me they DO care and know that the quality of one's life is so important. They know that if one is not sleeping well or able to take hold of their mind that these types of issues can have very adverse effects on the human body. The mind and the body have to be in tune with each other and when they aren't, it can truly cause things in the mind to reach out and attack the body.   The chronic pain community thanks you for that very generous gift that keeps is going and helps us to repair ourselves so that we may have better days and nights.   Having said this, now that things in my life have changed a little for the better, I will as of tonight finally switch over to the pro version as I have been wishing and hoping I could for so many years now.   Thank you also for keeping very decent prices so that we can eventually be able to get the full version for the optimal benefits. I hope that developers at IPNOS are aware of what a great service you are providing to so many people who are suffering very much.  I also have C-PTSD as many in the Chronic Pain community do. Living life in so much pain everyday of your life causes so much to happen to your mind that shows outwardly and very profoundly. Your app helps us to be able to attain better control of these issues.   I am also became a beta tester of the newest version. I really do love it! My fiancee has tinnitus that drives him up the wall frequently. He would close his eyes and shake his head in frustration of the high pitched droning in his head.   I tried him on the tinnitus portion and it does help him. He has not been able to get ANY relief from it till now. Thank you so much for the work you all put into this app! ‚ù§

replyContent:
Hello there

This can be fixed by changing the looping mode.

In the top menu select "More"
Inside the More section, select "Settings"
Inside the settings, select, "Loop Correction Mode"
Select MODE-4 or MODE-5
This should fix the problem.

If the problem persists please contact our support team through the help button or at support@ipnossoft.com

Hello Brennan

This can be fix by changing the looping mode. 

In the top menu select "More"
Inside the More section, select "Settings"
Inside the settings, select, "Loop Correction Mode"
Select MODE-4 or MODE-5
This should fix the problem. 

If the problem persist please contact our support team through the help button or at support@ipnossoft.com

replyContent:
Hello Jim

This can be fix by changing the looping mode. 

In the top menu select "More"
Inside the More section, select "Settings"
Inside the settings, select, "Loop Correction Mode"
Select MODE-4 or MODE-5
This should fix the problem. 

If the problem persist please contact our support team: http://support.ipnossoft.com
